{"number":401,"title":"ITALIAN HYMN","composer":"Arr. from Felice de Giardini","verses":[["Thou whose almighty Word","Chaos and darkness heard,","And took their flight;","Hear us, we humbly pray,","And where the Gospel-day","Sheds not its glorious ray,","Let there be light."],["Christ, thou dost come to bring","On thy redeeming wing","Healing and sight,","Health to the sick in mind,","Sight to the inly blind;","Ah, now to all mankind","Let there be light."],["Spirit of truth and love,","Life-giving, holy dove,","Speed forth thy flight;","Move on the waters’ face,","Bearing the lamp of grace,","And in earth’s darkest place","Let there be light."]]}